  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legal definitions typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Withdrawing the \"cleaned\" money as seemingly legitimate funds\n\nKey legal elements usually include:\n- Knowingly concealing the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Transforming illegal assets into apparently legal assets\n- Attempting to hide the true ownership or source of funds\n- Engaging in financial transactions to disguise illegal income\n\nSpecific definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most legal systems criminalize intentional money laundering activities.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
